<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TT1.6">
<l>paṭṭaṭi neṭṭukirp pāṟu kāṟpēy paruntoṭu kūkai pakaṇṭai yāntai</l>
<l>kuṭṭiyiṭa muṭṭai kūkaip pēykaḷ kuṟunari ceṉṟaṇaṅ kāṭu kāṭṭiṟ</l>
<l>piṭṭaṭit tuppuṟaṅ kāṭṭi liṭṭa piṇattiṉaip pērap puraṭṭi yāṅkē</l>
<l>yaṭṭamē pāyaniṉ ṟāṭu meṅka ḷappa ṉiṭamtiru vālaṅ kāṭē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The place of our father who dances constantly so as to spread in the eight [directions], wherever they turn over the corpse</l>
<l>put in the cremation ground outside so that it jumps [and] moves, in the cremation ground where owls with eggs,</l>
<l>demonesses, little jackals go [and] dance frightfully , while with tapping(?)  feet, long nails, ruined legs demonesses,</l>
<l>owls together with kites, Pakaṇṭais and spotted owlets knock their knuckles on their heads, is Tiruvalaṅkāṭu.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
